Residents of Kolonget village, Uasin Gishu County, yesterday woke up to shocking news of a man who hacked his wife to death before committing suicide.  John Kuria, 24, and his wife Diana Wekesa, 20, reportedly had domestic issues and had separated earlier this month.  While confirming the incident, Soy police commander Nehemiah Bitok said investigations are ongoing, adding that preliminary reports indicate that the couple had marital problems.  He said the bodies have been moved to Kitale County Hospital mortuary.     Uasin Gishu: Women storm, shut drinking dens in Kapkei  Sh20m treatment in India didn't help, Eldoret trip did  How foreign investor tapped gold in hay baling  Win for Kibor's sons as Court stops execution of eviction orders     Kenyans from Uasin Gishu county share their opinions on state of the Kenyan economy and the IMF loan  KTN Leo Nyanjani (26/04/2016): Ongezeko la mauaji ya kinyumbani  Panic in Uasin Gishu as villagers discover a coffin and human skeleton  By Lynn Kolongei | 12 hours ago By Obare Osinde | 14 hours ago By Gilbert Kimutai | 18 hours ago By Irissheel Shanzu | 2 days ago Uhuru unveils major plans for Nyanza ahead of visit